headline: Netflix is finally leaning into a key piece of the media playbook: Merchandising
summary: Netflix finally has a robust line-up of original intellectual property and is bolstering its merchandising strategy to keep fans engaged between releases.

headline: 2 Cash-Producing Stocks Worth Investigating and 1 That Underwhelm
summary: While strong cash flow is a key indicator of stability, it doesn’t always translate to superior returns. Some cash-heavy businesses struggle with inefficient spending, slowing demand, or weak competitive positioning.

headline: Does Warner Bros. Discovery’s 113% Rally Reflect Real Value After Streaming Merger Rumors?
summary: Curious if Warner Bros. Discovery’s massive run up reflects real value or just market buzz? You’re not alone, and you’re in exactly the right place to get answers. The stock has surged an impressive 113.3% year-to-date and is up 139.4% over the past 12 months, suggesting renewed optimism or shifting risk perspectives among investors.
